        <p style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700; font-size: 15px; font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 1px;">Home/Equity Loan Agreement</p>
        <br />
        <p>This Agreement is to be read with the Personal Customer Agreement. You acknowledge that your failure to comply with any terms and conditions of the Personal Customer Agreement will result in a default under the terms of this Agreement. </p>
        <br />
        <ol type="1">
          <li style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700; font-size: 15px; font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 1px;">
            How our Loan works</li>
        </ol>
        <p>Your Contribution should not be borrowed from any financial institution including those financial institutions not regulated by the Bank of Mauritius.</p>
        <br />
        <p>You will repay us by making the Instalments over an agreed period, with interest. You will also pay us the Fees and Charges associated with the Loan.</p>
        <br />
        <p>You agree to only use the Loan Amount for the Purpose stated above. We reserve the right to request evidence that the Loan Amount has been/is being used for the Purpose. Should we determine, at our sole discretion, that the Loan Amount, or any part thereof, has not been used for the Purpose, we reserve the right to cancel the Loan and demand immediate repayment of all amounts disbursed under the Loan.</p>
        <br />
        <p>Prior to disbursement of the Loan Amount: </p>
        <p>You can withdraw from this Agreement at any time as long as the Loan Amount has not been disbursed. The Bank will charge you an administrative fee in that respect.</p>
        <br />
        <p>In the event that the Conditions Precedent to Disbursement have not been satisfied or the facility has not been disbursed because of your acts and/or omissions within ninety (90) days as from signature of this Agreement or any such period of time as agreed between the Bank and you, the Bank reserves the right to cancel the Loan and withdraw from this Agreement at any time prior to the disbursement of the Loan Amount. The Bank will notify you at least 14 days before the cancellation takes effect. If you do not want the Loan to be cancelled, the Bank reserves the right to re-assess and review the terms and conditions of the Loan and to request that you submit a fresh application.</p>
        <br />
        <p>The Bank reserves the right to review and re-assess the terms and conditions of the Loan or rescind the whole agreement prior to drawdown of the loan should the Bank be made aware of any adverse information surrounding the Borrower’s situation, which in the opinion of the Bank has or is reasonably likely to have a material adverse effect on your ability to perform any of your obligations under this Agreement.</p>
        <br />
        <ol start="2" type="1">
          <li style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700; font-size: 15px; font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 1px;">
  
            Our Agreement</li>
        </ol>
        <p>In the rest of these terms we refer to:</p>
        <ul type="disc">
          <li>this Loan agreement as this ‘Agreement’;</li>
          <li>the asset given as security as the ‘Property’; and</li>
          <li>your transactional bank account with us as ‘your Account’. </li>
        </ul>
        <br />
        <p>The Loan shall be available for the first drawdown for a period of 3 months, from the date of your acceptance of the terms of this Agreement.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:19.85pt; text-align:justify; line-height:normal; font-size:10pt"> <br /> </p>
        <ol start="3" type="1">
          <li style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700; font-size: 15px; font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 1px;">Your Loan Amount</li>
        </ol>
        <p>You agree that your Loan Amount will be either:</p>
        <ul type="disc">
          <li>The amount you applied for; or </li>
          <li>such lower amount as we may determine following an assessment of your ability to repay your Loan Amount, provided that this amount will not be more than 60% or 70% or 80% of our valuation of the Property (as may be applicable to your case). </li>
        </ul>
        <br />
        <p>You will be required to open a transactional account with us if you do not already have one and you will be required to deposit enough funds in that account so that we can deduct any upfront fees before we will make the Loan available to you. If you are employed, your salary must be paid into your Account during the term of this Agreement unless your employer deducts your Instalments from your salary before it is paid to you. If you are self-employed, your business income must be routed to your Account during the term of this Agreement. If, during the Term of the Loan, the payment of your salary or income into your Account is stopped or discontinued, the Bank reserves the right to re-assess the terms and conditions of the Loan, including but not limited to the interest rate.</p>
        <br />
        <p>We will make payment of your Loan Amount, or any tranche thereof, to your nominated payees/beneficiaries upon successful transcription of your sale deed or registration of the Security at the Conservator of Mortgages (as may be applicable to your case), and/or upon us being satisfied that you have met the Conditions Precedent to Disbursement.</p>
        <br />
        <p>If we require you to pay off an existing debt to a credit provider as a condition of your Loan, you must obtain a statement for us from the credit provider showing how much is required to pay off the debt, and we will give you a cheque (or make a direct payment) to the credit provider, and pay any remainder of your Loan to you.</p>
        <br />
        <p>You agree to notify us in writing if you take up additional credit facilities with another credit provider during the term of this Agreement.</p>
        <br />
  
        <ol start="4" type="1">
          <li style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700; font-size: 15px; font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 1px;">Instalments </li>
        </ol>
        <p>You must pay the Instalments to repay the Loan Amount. Your Instalments will be deducted from your Account, by debit order, on a monthly basis on the agreed Instalment date. You acknowledge that based on your actual date of disbursement of the Loan, there may be a residual amount left unpaid after the repayment of your last instalment and you undertake to repay us such residual amount.</p>
        <br />
        <p>You agree to tell us and any additional credit providers if you are unable to pay an Instalment on the Instalment date (including the reason why you are not able to pay the Instalment). You must seek our agreement regarding arrangements for the payment of the Instalment in default.</p>
        <br />
        <p>If we need to change the date of your Instalment, we will notify you at least 7 business days before the date upon which the change will occur. </p>
        <br />
        <p>If any sum falls due for payment on a day which is not a Business Day it shall be made on the immediately preceding Business Day. </p>
        <br />
        <ol start="5" type="1">
          <li style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700; font-size: 15px; font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 1px;">
            Interest, fees and costs</li>
        </ol>
        <p>You agree to pay Interest, Fees and Costs as stated or referred to in this Agreement and the Personal Customer Agreement.</p>
        <br />
        <p>You will pay interest on your Loan Amount, for the period of this Agreement, starting on the day that the Loan Amount is paid out to you. Interest will be calculated daily, on the outstanding balance of the Loan Amount, and will be charged to the Loan Account on a monthly basis.</p>
        <br />
        <p>The interest rate on your Loan Amount is variable and will change as the reference rate changes. The reference rate can be either our “Prime Lending Rate” or the “Key Rate”. If the Reference Rate is less than zero, the Interest shall be deemed to be zero.</p>
        <br />
        <p>Depending on our prevailing offer, we may agree that a fixed interest rate be applied to your Loan Amount for a certain period. When the period of your fixed interest rate expires, the interest rate applicable to your Loan Amount will automatically change to the Variable Interest Rate in this Agreement, unless we have agreed to extend the fixed rate period.</p>
        <br />
        <p>You will be notified by us, of changes in our Reference Rate and the adjusted amount of your Instalment within at least 45 days after the changes take effect. In the event that our Reference Rate is increased, you have the option of deciding whether to either increase your monthly Instalment or extend the Term of the Loan, keeping your monthly Instalment unchanged, provided such extension of Term would not exceed your retirement age. In the event that our Reference Rate is decreased, you have the option of either maintaining the Term of the Loan by requesting a revised monthly Instalment amount or you can decrease the Term of the Loan by retaining the agreed monthly Instalment amount. </p>
        <br />
        <p>If you default, you will pay a default interest rate of 2 per cent, wherever applicable, calculated on the default instalment capital excluding interest payable thereon. To the extent that Section 16(3) of the Borrower Protection Act is applicable, you will not pay a default interest.</p>
