        <p>You understand that it is a condition of this Agreement that you provide us with the Property as Security and any Additional Security (where necessary).</p>
        <br />
        <p>Any breach or default of any term or condition contained in the Security or Additional Security documentation shall be considered a default under this Agreement.</p>
        <br />
        <p>You may be requested to cancel any existing security which burdens the Property. Any asset used as Security or Additional Security for your Loan Amount may not be used as security for any other purpose or transaction without our written consent. </p>
        <br />
        <p>Where the requested Security is a charge over the Property, you understand that our attorneys will draft the necessary documentation and attend to the registration of the charge at your cost. </p>
        <br />
        <p>If you choose not to accept this Agreement, after we have approved your Loan Amount but before the Security is registered or recorded against the Property, you will be responsible for the administrative and related costs incurred by us during that time. </p>
        <br />
        <p>We may request, at any time during the term of this Agreement, that the Property and any Additional Security be evaluated, by our approved valuer, at your cost. We may require you to provide us with further Additional Security during the term of this Agreement if we believe that the Property and any Additional Security provided are no longer sufficient. </p>
        <br />
        <ol start="7" type="1">
          <li style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700; font-size: 15px; font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 1px;">Property</li>
        </ol>
        <p>You understand that we require the Property to be valued by our approved valuer, at your cost, to enable us to assess the value of our Security. This valuation does not include an inspection on the structural condition or any other condition of the Property by us. You agree that such valuation fee is to be paid upfront into your Account with us, and is not refundable.</p>
        <br />
        <p>You agree that it is your responsibility to maintain the quality of the Property and to ensure that no changes, relating to the usage, zoning or anything that may negatively affect the Property, are made to the Property without our prior written consent. If we agree to any change to the Property, you must notify us in writing of the changes made to the Property and adjust your insurance policy to accommodate the changes made to the Property accordingly. The Bank reserves the right to re-evaluate the Property as and when it is deemed required during the Term of the Loan. This valuation may include an inspection of the Property. The Bank will give you at least 7 days’ notice before doing such a valuation to which you hereby give your consent. Any such revaluation may be done at your costs.</p>
        <br />
        <p> <br /> </p>
        <ol start="8" type="1">
          <li style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700; font-size: 15px; font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 1px;">Transfer of rights by you to us involving the Property</li>
        </ol>
        <p>You agree to pledge any rentals or other income receivable from the Property being acquired in favour of the bank until final repayment of your Loan. The Bank may apply its right of set-off against such rentals or income receivable in case of default on your Loan.</p>
        <br />
        <p>If the Property is acquired by government or any third party rights are registered against the Property during this Agreement, you agree to transfer, as additional security, all claims (including compensation) as a result of the acquisition or third party rights registration against the Property. The additional security will however be limited to the outstanding amount on your Loan.</p>
        <br />
        <ol start="9" type="1">
          <li style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700; font-size: 15px; font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 1px;">Transfer of our rights and obligations in terms of this Agreement</li>
        </ol>
        <p>You agree that we may, at any time, transfer any or all of our rights and obligations as per the terms and conditions of this Agreement, including the Security and the Additional Security, to a third party of our choice. </p>
        <br />
        <ol start="10" type="1">
          <li style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700; font-size: 15px; font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 1px;"> Insurance </li>
        </ol>
        <p>You understand that it is an additional condition of this Agreement that you take up a Decreasing Term Assurance for a minimum amount corresponding to your Loan amount, to insure against the possibility of your death or total and permanent disability during the term of this Agreement. You are also required to take up, where applicable, Fire and Allied Perils Insurance (in respect of the Property) for an amount not less than the value of the replacement cost of the Property for the term of this Agreement. </p>
        <br />
        <p>You will be required to provide us with proof that you have taken up the required insurance policies and you agree to pay the said insurance premiums on a monthly or yearly basis, as may be applicable, for the duration of this Agreement. The proceeds of the insurance policies will be assigned to us.</p>
        <br />
        <p>Pursuant to Section 81 of the Insurance Act 2005, you have a free choice as to the insurance policy required to guarantee this Loan. The insurance policy to be provided can take the form of (1) a new insurance policy; (2) an existing insurance policy; or (3) a combination of the aforementioned two. By signing this Agreement, you hereby confirm that you have been informed of your right to this free choice under Section 81 of the Insurance Act 2005 and that you have exercised this right freely and willingly.</p>
        <br />
        <p>In the event that you fail to renew or maintain the required insurance cover during the term of this Agreement, you authorise us to pay the insurance premium on your behalf by debiting your Account or your Loan account.</p>
        <br />
        <p>You will be required to set up a standing order in respect of the insurance premiums to be paid from your Account.</p>
        <br />
        <p>In lieu of assigning the proceeds of a Decreasing Term Assurance, you also have the option of assigning in our favour the proceeds of any other Life Insurance cover, acceptable to us.</p>
        <br />
        <p>You will notify us of any event which may give rise to a claim under any insurance policy assigned with respect to your Loan.</p>
        <br />
        <ol start="11" type="1">
          <li style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700; font-size: 15px; font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 1px;">
            Pre-payments and paying off your Loan Account early</li>
        </ol>
        <p>At any time you can pay Instalments early or pay the outstanding balance of your Loan Account in full.</p>
        <br />
        <p>If you want to pay off the full outstanding balance you must inform us, and we will give you a statement telling you how much you owe. </p>
        <br />
        <br />
        <br />
        <br />
        <ol start="12" type="1">
          <li style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700; font-size: 15px; font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 1px;"> Default </li>
        </ol>
        <p>You will be in default under the terms of this Agreement if:</p>
        <ol type="a">
          <li>
  
            Non-Payment: you do not pay an Instalment in full by the Instalment date and such failure to pay continues for a period of:
            <ol type="i">
              <li> three (3) months if Instalments must be repaid on a monthly basis; or </li>
              <li> six (6) months if Instalments must be repaid at intervals other than on a monthly basis; or</li>
            </ol>
          </li>
          <li>
  
            Obligations under the Finance Documents: You do not comply with your obligations under the Finance Documents;</li>
          <li>
  
            Other Obligations: You do not comply with your obligations under any other credit facilities and/or ancillary facilities agreements which you already have with us and/or which you may have with us after signature of this Agreement;</li>
          <li>
  
            Bankruptcy/Insolvency:
            <ol type="i">
              <li>
                You are deemed to be bankrupt;</li>
              <li>
  
                We have reason to believe that an Obligor is, or is likely to become, bankrupt of insolvent;</li>
              <li>
  
                An Obligor is unable, or admits inability to pay its debts when due or suspends making payment on any of its debts; or by reason of actual or anticipated financial difficulties, commences negotiations with one or more of his creditors with a view to rescheduling any of his indebtedness;</li>
              <li>
  
                The value of the assets of an Obligor is less than its liabilities (considering contingent and prospective liabilities);</li>
            </ol>
          </li>
          <li> A decision of a competent authority is delivered against an Obligor’s assets;</li>
          <li> Misrepresentation: Any representation, warranty or undertaking made by you or the Guarantor in the Finance Documents or any other document delivered by or on your behalf or on behalf of the Guarantor under or in connection with any Finance Document is or proves to have been incorrect or misleading in any material respect when made or deemed to be made.; is not complied with; or ceases to be true;</li>
          <li>
            Unlawfulness and invalidity:
            <ol type="i">
              <li> It is or it becomes unlawful for an Obligor to perform any of your obligations under the Finance Documents;</li>
              <li> Any obligation or obligations of any Obligor under any Finance Documents are not or cease to be legal, valid, binding or enforceable and the cessation individually or cumulatively materially and adversely affects the interests of the Bank under the Finance Documents;</li>
              <li>
                Any Finance Document ceases to be in full force and effect or is alleged by a party to it (other than the Bank) to be ineffective;</li>
            </ol>
          </li>
          <li> Repudiation: An Obligor rescinds or purports to rescind or repudiates or purports to repudiate a Finance Document or evidences an intention to rescind or repudiate a Finance Document;</li>
          <li>Litigation: Any litigation, arbitration, administrative, governmental, regulatory or other investigations, proceedings or disputes are commenced or threatened in relation to the Finance Documents or the transactions contemplated in the Finance Documents or against any Obligor or its assets which have or are reasonably likely to have a Material Adverse Effect. </li>
          <li> Material Adverse Effect: Any event or circumstance occurs which the Bank reasonably believes has or is reasonably likely to have a Material Adverse Effect. </li>
        </ol>
        <p>In this Agreement, unless the context otherwise requires the following definitions shall apply:</p>
        <br />
        <p>“Finance Document” means this Agreement, the Personal Customer Agreement, any security document entered into in relation to this Loan and any other document designated as such by the Bank and the Borrower.</p>
        <br />
        <p>“Material Adverse Effect” means in the reasonable opinion of the Bank, a material adverse effect on:</p>
        <ol type="a">
          <li> the business, operations, property, condition (financial or otherwise) or prospects of any party to this Agreement or the Finance Documents; or</li>
          <li>
  
            the ability of any Obligor to perform any of its obligations under the Finance Documents; or</li>
          <li>
            the validity or enforceability of any of the Finance Documents or the rights or remedies of the Bank under any of the Finance Documents.</li>
        </ol>
        <p>“Obligor” means the Borrower, the Guarantor(s) (if named in the Commercial Terms) and any other person who has given a guarantee or security relating to this Agreement. </p>
        <ol start="13" type="1">
          <li style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700; font-size: 15px; font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 1px;"> Consequences of Default</li>
        </ol>
        <p>If you default in any of your obligations under this Agreement or any agreement governing an existing/Ancillary facility with us, we have the right to contact any referee, employer or the Mauritius Credit Information Bureau and to make any such enquiry or disclosure as may be deemed appropriate by us.</p>
        <br />
        <p>If you default in any of your obligations under this Agreement or any agreement we may end this Agreement by written notification to you requiring you to pay the full outstanding balance of your Loan Account within 14 business days after the delivery of the notification, with Interest charged at the Default Interest Rate, Fees and Costs. On the expiry of this notification we may exercise our rights in terms of the Security and Additional Security provided under this Agreement.</p>
        <br />
        <p>In the context of a default, you will be responsible for the attorney's fees reasonably expended by us by way of court initiated proceedings in order to recover any outstanding balance of the Loan Account.</p>
        <br />
        <ol start="14" type="1">
          <li style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700; font-size: 15px; font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 1px;"> Disclosure to guarantors</li>
        </ol>
        <p>The below part concerns the guarantors and is aligned to the requirement of the Guideline on Disclosure of Information to Guarantors as issued by the Bank of Mauritius. </p>
        <br />
        <h4> As a guarantor, your rights in relation and liabilities are as follows:</h4>
  
        <p style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700; font-size: 15px; font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 1px;">Your rights</p>
        <ol type="a">
          <li>Request for a copy of the contract pertaining to the above security signed by yourself at any time on or after signature of the contract;</li>
          <li>Make enquiries from the MCIB on information which has been registered in your name by the Bank;</li>
          <li>Make a complaint if you feel aggrieved by the acts or omissions of the Bank by calling our Service Centre on the (+230) 402 1000;</li>
          <li>Submit a request for a statement of account related to the credit facility at any time during the credit facility period;</li>
          <li>Seek legal advice pertaining to the above security to understand the commitment and the potential consequences of entering into this contract at your own cost and expenses.</li>
        </ol>
  
        <p style="color: #DC0032; font-weight: 700; font-size: 15px; font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: 1px;">Your Liabilities</p>
        <ol type="a">
          <li>You have bound yourself for the Borrower’s debt and you undertake to honour the credit obligations of the Borrower in case of impaired credits;</li>
          <li>In case the Borrower fails to pay, you are liable for Borrower’s debt which may include accrued interest, as specified in the contract pertaining to the security;</li>
          <li>In case the Borrower fails to pay, you are liable for the liabilities of the Borrower pertaining to the security and;</li>
          <li>You will be rendered liable under the contract if the Borrower is in default of any payment to the Bank and the Bank makes a demand on the Guarantor.</li>
        </ol>
        <br />
        <br />
